Hourglass Capital LLC Has $6,486,000 Stake in Oracle Corporation (ORCL)

Posted by Vince Mercandetti on Jul 27th, 2017 // No Comments 

Hourglass Capital LLC maintained its position in Oracle Corporation (NYSE:ORCL) during the first quarter, according to its most recent 13F filing with the SEC. The fund owned 145,397 shares of the enterprise software provider’s stock at the end of the first quarter. Oracle Corporation comprises 1.6% of Hourglass Capital LLC’s investment portfolio, making the stock its 25th largest position. Hourglass Capital LLC’s holdings in Oracle Corporation were worth $6,486,000 as of its most recent SEC filing. 
Several other hedge funds and other institutional investors have also recently added to or reduced their stakes in ORCL. Menora Mivtachim Holdings LTD. raised its position in Oracle Corporation by 31.2% in the fourth quarter. Menora Mivtachim Holdings LTD. now owns 567,490 shares of the enterprise software provider’s stock valued at $21,820,000 after buying an additional 135,100 shares in the last quarter. Horizon Kinetics LLC raised its position in Oracle Corporation by 6.9% in the fourth quarter. Horizon Kinetics LLC now owns 11,206 shares of the enterprise software provider’s stock valued at $431,000 after buying an additional 721 shares in the last quarter. Ladenburg Thalmann Financial Services Inc. raised its position in Oracle Corporation by 5.4% in the fourth quarter. Ladenburg Thalmann Financial Services Inc. now owns 152,812 shares of the enterprise software provider’s stock valued at $5,885,000 after buying an additional 7,866 shares in the last quarter. HCR Wealth Advisors purchased a new position in Oracle Corporation during the fourth quarter valued at approximately $384,000. Finally, Guggenheim Capital LLC raised its position in Oracle Corporation by 25.2% in the fourth quarter. Guggenheim Capital LLC now owns 1,798,238 shares of the enterprise software provider’s stock valued at $69,142,000 after buying an additional 361,791 shares in the last quarter. Institutional investors and hedge funds own 58.65% of the company’s stock. 




Shares of Oracle Corporation (NYSE ORCL) opened at 51.17 on Thursday. The stock has a market cap of $211.67 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 23.15 and a beta of 1.07. The stock’s 50 day moving average price is $48.46 and its 200 day moving average price is $44.45. Oracle Corporation has a 52 week low of $37.62 and a 52 week high of $51.85. 


 Get Oracle Corporation alerts:



Oracle Corporation (NYSE:ORCL) last posted its quarterly earnings data on Wednesday, June 21st. The enterprise software provider reported $0.89 EPS for the quarter, beating the Zacks’ consensus estimate of $0.78 by $0.11. Oracle Corporation had a net margin of 24.74% and a return on equity of 20.90%. The business had revenue of $10.94 billion for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $10.45 billion. During the same quarter last year, the business earned $0.81 earnings per share. The business’s revenue for the quarter was up 3.3% on a year-over-year basis. Equities research analysts anticipate that Oracle Corporation will post $2.96 EPS for the current fiscal year. 
The business also recently disclosed a quarterly dividend, which will be paid on Wednesday, August 2nd. Investors of record on Wednesday, July 19th will be paid a dividend of $0.19 per share. The ex-dividend date of this dividend is Monday, July 17th. This represents a $0.76 dividend on an annualized basis and a dividend yield of 1.49%. Oracle Corporation’s dividend payout ratio is presently 34.55%. 
